// clz(x0) — count leading zero bits of the 64-bit value in x0,
// return in x0 (clz(0) = 64). ARM64 has a native CLZ instruction,
// so this is the smallest possible leaf: one op + ret. Pure
// register; no relocation, no memory, no arena state, no HexaVal
// touch — a foundational bit-op leaf (B9.6a / F3 increment 4).
//
// Algorithm:
//   clz x0, x0
//   ret
