// ── rt_ctz ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
// ctz(x0) — count trailing zero bits of the 64-bit value in x0,
// return in x0 (ctz(0) = 64). ARM64 has no direct CTZ, so we
// bit-reverse (RBIT) then count leading zeros (CLZ): the leading
// zeros of the reversed word equal the trailing zeros of the
// original. Pure register; no relocation, no memory, no arena
// state, no HexaVal touch (B9.6a / F3 increment 4).
//
// Algorithm:
//   rbit x0, x0          ; reverse bit order
//   clz x0, x0           ; trailing zeros of orig = leading zeros of reversed
//   ret
//
// 3 instructions, 12 bytes. Encodings validated against
// `as -arch arm64` disassembly (B9.6a self-emit increment 4).

fn rt_ctz() {
